two people are playing a game.

their names are Alice and Bob.

the game is this:

there's a list of numbers.

the list contains a mix of positive and negative numbers.

the players, Alice and Bob, take turns picking numbers from this list.

there's two rules to picking from this list:
    what part of the list they can pick from?
    how many they can pick?

they must always pick from the start of the list.

they can either pick 
    one number, 
    two consecutive numbers, OR,
    three consecutive numbers.

the game ends when they are no more numbers to pick.

at which point, the result is determined.


